abstract.text: Represents a generic overlay that draws its contents using a Core Graphics path data type.

inlineContent.text: You can use this class to implement simple path-based overlay views or subclass it to define additional drawing behaviors. The default drawing behavior of this class is to apply the object’s current fill attributes, fill the path, apply the current stroke attributes, and then stroke the path.
If you subclass, you should override the
method and use that method to build the appropriate path for the overlay. You can invalidate this path as needed and force the path to be recreated using whatever new data your subclass has obtained.
In iOS 7 and later, use the
class to display path-based overlays instead.
